According to the organization itself, a “B Corp Certification is a designation that a business is meeting high standards of verified performance, accountability, and transparency on factors from employee benefits and charitable giving to supply chain practices and input materials.”

Kudos to @patagonia — the OG B Corp — for “going purpose” instead of “going public” and putting their company in a trust to protect the planet with its $100 million annual profit.

Here I am standing on art made from fallen trees after I passed even more fallen trees after the most recent storm. Our world is falling apart, and I’m grateful companies have the space to do better 🌍

