COP: Conference of the Parties. 

According to the UN:”The COP is the supreme decision-making body of the Convention.“

They first met in Bonn, Germany in 1995. 
They now meet in Sharm El Sheikh, Egypt in 2022, starting today.

COP27 will focus on three main areas:
✔️Reducing emissions
✔️Helping countries to prepare for and deal with climate change
✔️Securing technical support and funding for developing countries for the above

After a record-breaking year for extreme temperatures, rain, and lack of rain, their agenda feels like it’s too little, too late.

Even though representatives from BRICS and developed nations are attending, I don’t feel entirely convinced these major players are putting the climate above 💵💶💷💴 

Right now my hope for significant change is 50/50 🤞🏽 We’ve had 27 years to get our act together officially.

📷: @sayonickerson 
