India’s journey to International Day of Yoga 2026 is inspiring a global wave of wellness, participation, and collective consciousness.
With every countdown milestone, the message of Yoga is reaching people across regions, generations, and nations — promoting harmony between mind, body, and spirit.

From New Delhi’s launch of Yoga 365 and special Yoga protocols for NCDs, to record-breaking participation in Maharashtra and Telangana, the movement continues to grow stronger with each passing day.
As the nation now gears up for the 25-day countdown and Yoga Mahotsav 2026 in the iconic heritage city of Khajuraho, the spirit of Yoga continues to unite communities through wellness, culture, and shared purpose.

The road to IDY 2026 is not just a countdown — it is a celebration of India’s wellness legacy and a commitment towards a healthier world.

