In the lead up to the 12th International Day of Yoga on 21st June, the High Commission of India in Lilongwe hosted a special yoga session on 16 May 2026 at the iconic National Memorial Park (National War Memorial) as a curtain raiser to the upcoming International Day of Yoga (IDY) 2026 on 21 June 2026. 

The session brought together yoga enthusiasts and people from all age groups, highlighting the spirit of wellness, harmony and holistic living as the countdown to IDY begins.

His Worship Peter Alex Banda, Mayor of Lilongwe City Council graced the occasion as Guest of Honour. 

High Commissioner, in his remarks, described yoga as a holistic practice that combines physical postures, breathing techniques and meditation and is essential for overall well-being.

The Mayor, in his remarks, said Yoga is a gift from India to the world. He also mentioned that Yoga costs nothing, yet it offers many benefits, including good health, reduced stress and peace of mind. 

The event was attended by large number of people including diplomats, school children, friends of India, members of Indian community among others. 

